Background: This project wraps pflag and cobra so that very little of these libraries are visible or usable on the seam. The goal is to make testing much better for users.

The @richtext/  package's `Theme` logic is a bit over-engineered right now. We're using reflection to look up fields on a struct, but really it's just the name of a label to type.

Instead, lets change this theme so that:

* It no longer uses reflection
* It no longer takes `any`, it takes `map[string]style.Style`
* The function no longer returns an error, but it can panic if a field name isn't valid. Ensure this is documented.

For this plan, you ONLY need to know the richtext/ directories, nothing outside of it.

